</section>

<section class="product-desc-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="product-desc-grid">
      <div class="product-desc">
        <div class="section-tag">Product Overview</div>
        <div class="divider"></div>
        <h2>The Natural Solution for <span>Sustainable</span> Agriculture</h2>
        <p>Agricultural sepiolite is a specially graded product designed for the farming and agrochemical industries. Its unique combination of high absorption capacity, controlled porosity, and chemical inertness makes it an ideal carrier substrate for fertilizers, herbicides, pesticides, and seed coatings.</p>
        <p>When used as a soil amendment, sepiolite significantly improves soil structure in sandy and clay-heavy soils alike. Its porous fiber structure increases water retention capacity by up to 30%, reducing irrigation frequency and improving drought resilience for crops.</p>
        <p>As a fertilizer carrier, sepiolite enables slow-release nutrient delivery. Active ingredients are adsorbed into the mineral's micropore network and released gradually over weeks, improving nutrient efficiency and reducing the environmental impact of agricultural runoff.</p>
        <p>Our agricultural grade meets the quality standards required by major agrochemical manufacturers and is certified for organic farming applications in the European Union. We supply to clients across Europe, the Middle East, and Africa.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="tech-specs-card">
          <h3>
            <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><path d="M10 2L18 7V13L10 18L2 13V7L10 2Z" stroke="#C9922A" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/><circle cx="10" cy="10" r="3" fill="#C9922A"/></svg>
            Technical Specifications
          </h3>
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="spec-label">Product Form</span>
            <span class="spec-value">Granules / Powder</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="spec-label">Size Range</span>
            <span class="spec-value">0.5–4 mm (granules)</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="spec-label">Absorption Capacity</span>
            <span class="spec-value">≥ 120% by weight</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="spec-label">MgO</span>
            <span class="spec-value">≥ 18%</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="spec-label">SiO₂</span>
            <span class="spec-value">≥ 54%</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="spec-label">Moisture</span>
            <span class="spec-value">≤ 12%</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="spec-label">pH</span>
            <span class="spec-value">7.5–9.0</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="spec-label">CEC</span>
            <span class="spec-value">20–30 meq/100g</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="spec-label">Heavy Metals</span>
            <span class="spec-value">Below EU limits</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="spec-label">Color</span>
            <span class="spec-value">White to Cream</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="spec-label">Packaging</span>
            <span class="spec-value">25kg / 1 MT Bags</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="spec-label">Delivery</span>
            <span class="spec-value">FOB Mersin / Samsun</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="usage-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="usage-header">
      <div class="section-tag" style="color:var(--gold-light);">Applications</div>
      <div class="divider divider--center"></div>
      <h2 class="section-title" style="color:var(--white);">Where Agricultural Sepiolite <span>Is Used</span></h2>
    </div>
    <div class="usage-grid">
      <div class="usage-card reveal">
        <div class="usage-icon">🌾</div>
        <h3>Fertilizer Carriers</h3>
        <p>Sepiolite granules serve as an inert carrier that absorbs liquid and solid fertilizers, enabling uniform field application and controlled nutrient release over the growing season.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="usage-card reveal">
        <div class="usage-icon">🌱</div>
        <h3>Soil Conditioning</h3>
        <p>Mixed into soil to improve water retention, aeration, and cation exchange capacity. Particularly effective in sandy soils where water and nutrient leaching is a challenge.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="usage-card reveal">
        <div class="usage-icon">🧪</div>
        <h3>Pesticide & Herbicide Delivery</h3>
        <p>Provides controlled-release delivery of crop protection chemicals. The micropore network holds active ingredients and releases them gradually, reducing application frequency.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="usage-card reveal">
        <div class="usage-icon">🌿</div>
        <h3>Organic Farming</h3>
        <p>Certified for use in organic agriculture as a natural soil amendment. Improves root zone conditions without introducing synthetic chemicals or heavy metals.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="usage-card reveal">
        <div class="usage-icon">🌻</div>
        <h3>Seed Coating & Pelleting</h3>
        <p>Used as a coating material for seeds to improve handling, protect against disease, and deliver micronutrients directly to the germinating plant.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="usage-card reveal">
        <div class="usage-icon">🐄</div>
        <h3>Animal Bedding</h3>
        <p>Agricultural sepiolite granules make excellent livestock bedding — highly absorbent, dust-free, and naturally odor-controlling for healthy barn environments.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="advantages-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="advantages-grid">
      <div>
        <div class="section-tag">Why Choose Us</div>
        <div class="divider"></div>
        <h2 class="section-title">Key <span>Advantages</span></h2>
        <div class="advantage-list">
          <div class="advantage-item reveal">
            <div class="advantage-num">01</div>
            <div>
              <strong>Slow-Release Efficiency</strong>
              <p>Nutrients are held in the micropore network and released gradually — improving fertilizer utilization rates by up to 25% compared to direct application.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="advantage-item reveal">
            <div class="advantage-num">02</div>
            <div>
              <strong>Water Retention Boost</strong>
              <p>When mixed into soil at 5–10% by volume, sepiolite increases water holding capacity by up to 30%, reducing irrigation needs in arid climates.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="advantage-item reveal">
            <div class="advantage-num">03</div>
            <div>
              <strong>Organic Certified</strong>
              <p>Our agricultural grade meets EU organic farming standards, providing a natural, chemical-free solution for environmentally conscious producers.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="advantage-item reveal">
            <div class="advantage-num">04</div>
            <div>
              <strong>Reduced Chemical Runoff</strong>
              <p>Controlled-release delivery of pesticides and fertilizers significantly reduces environmental contamination of groundwater and waterways.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="advantage-item reveal">
            <div class="advantage-num">05</div>
            <div>
              <strong>Versatile Application</strong>
              <p>Available in both granular and powder form to suit different application methods — broadcast spreading, drill seeding, or direct soil incorporation.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="advantage-image">
        <img width="960" height="1280" src="/images/mine/mine-landscape-12.webp" alt="Sepiolite mine – Zamana Turkey" loading="lazy" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="faq-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="faq-header">
      <div class="section-tag">Common Questions</div>
      <div class="divider divider--center"></div>
      <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked <span>Questions</span></h2>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          Is agricultural sepiolite safe for organic farming?
          <svg class="faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><path d="M5 7.5L10 12.5L15 7.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">
          Yes, our agricultural grade is certified for organic farming use in the EU. It is a naturally occurring mineral with no synthetic additives or chemical treatments.
        </div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          What application rate is recommended for soil conditioning?
          <svg class="faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><path d="M5 7.5L10 12.5L15 7.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">
          Typical application is 5–10% by volume mixed into the root zone. For sandy soils, higher rates provide greater benefit. Our technical team can advise for your specific soil type.
        </div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          Can sepiolite be used with liquid fertilizers?
          <svg class="faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><path d="M5 7.5L10 12.5L15 7.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">
          Yes, sepiolite granules readily absorb liquid fertilizers and convert them into a dry, free-flowing product that is easy to handle, store, and apply with standard equipment.
        </div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          Does sepiolite affect soil pH?
          <svg class="faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><path d="M5 7.5L10 12.5L15 7.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">
          Sepiolite has a slightly alkaline pH (7.5–9.0) which can be beneficial for acidic soils. In neutral to alkaline soils, the effect is minimal at recommended application rates.
        </div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          What is the minimum order for agricultural sepiolite?
          <svg class="faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><path d="M5 7.5L10 12.5L15 7.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">
          Minimum order is 20 metric tons. Seasonal contracts and annual supply agreements are available with preferential pricing for agricultural distributors.
        </div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="related-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="related-header">
      <div class="section-tag">More Products</div>
      <div class="divider divider--center"></div>
      <h2 class="section-title">Explore Our Other <span>Grades</span></h2>
    </div>
    <div class="related-grid">
      <div class="related-card reveal">
        <div class="related-card-img">
          <img width="506" height="900" src="/images/products/product-raw-ore.webp" alt="Raw Sepiolite Ore" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
        <div class="related-card-body">
          <h3>Raw Sepiolite Ore</h3>
          <p>Directly mined sepiolite in natural block form with natural fiber structure intact.</p>
          <a href="../raw-sepiolite-ore/" class="related-link">View Product <svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none"><path d="M3 8h10M9 4l4 4-4 4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg></a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="related-card reveal">
        <div class="related-card-img">
          <img width="675" height="900" src="/images/products/product-granulated.webp" alt="Granulated Sepiolite" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
        <div class="related-card-body">
          <h3>Granulated Sepiolite</h3>
          <p>Precision-sized granules for cat litter, agriculture, and industrial absorbents.</p>
          <a href="../granulated-sepiolite/" class="related-link">View Product <svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none"><path d="M3 8h10M9 4l4 4-4 4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg></a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="related-card reveal">
        <div class="related-card-img">
          <img width="1200" height="896" src="/images/products/product-construction.webp" alt="Construction & Insulation Grade" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
        <div class="related-card-body">
          <h3>Construction & Insulation Grade</h3>
          <p>Sepiolite for insulating boards, fireproof coatings, and building materials.</p>
          <a href="../construction-insulation-grade/" class="related-link">View Product <svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none"><path d="M3 8h10M9 4l4 4-4 4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg></a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>





<script defer>
  function switchImage(thumb, src, alt) {
    document.getElementById('mainImgSrc').src = src;
    document.getElementById('mainImgSrc').alt = alt;
    document.querySelectorAll('.product-thumb').forEach(function(t) { t.classList.remove('active'); });
    thumb.classList.add('active');
  }
  function toggleFaq(el) {
    var item = el.parentElement;
    var wasOpen = item.classList.contains('open');
    document.querySelectorAll('.faq-item').forEach(function(i) { i.classList.remove('open'); });
    if (!wasOpen) item.classList.add('open');
  }
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function () {
    var revealObserver = new IntersectionObserver(function(entries) {
      entries.forEach(function(e) {
        if (e.isIntersecting) { e.target.classList.add('visible'); revealObserver.unobserve(e.target); }
      });
    }, { threshold: 0.12 });
    document.querySelectorAll('.reveal').forEach(function(el) { revealObserver.observe(el); });
    var navbar = document.getElementById('navbar');
    if (navbar) {
      window.addEventListener('scroll', function() { navbar.classList.toggle('scrolled', window.scrollY > 60); }, { passive: true });
    }
    document.addEventListener('click', function(e) {
      var ham = e.target.closest('#hamburger');
      if (ham) {
        var menu = document.getElementById('mobileMenu');
        var isOpen = menu && menu.classList.toggle('open');
        ham.setAttribute('aria-expanded', isOpen ? 'true' : 'false');
        if (menu) menu.setAttribute('aria-hidden', isOpen ? 'false' : 'true');
      }
      if (e.target.closest('#mobileMenu a')) {
        var menu2 = document.getElementById('mobileMenu');
        var ham2  = document.getElementById('hamburger');
        if (menu2) { menu2.classList.remove('open'); menu2.setAttribute('aria-hidden','true'); }
        if (ham2)  { ham2.setAttribute('aria-expanded','false'); }
      }
    });
  });
</script>
</Layout>

<style is:global>
/* ===== PRODUCT HERO ===== */
    .product-hero {
      padding: 3.5rem 0 4rem;
      background: var(--cream);
    }
    .product-hero-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 3.5rem;
      align-items: start;
    }
    .product-gallery {
      position: sticky;
      top: 80px;
    }
    .product-main-img {
      border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
      overflow: hidden;
      aspect-ratio: 4/3;
      background: var(--white);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
      border: 1px solid var(--cream-dark);
    }
    .product-main-img img {
      width: 100%;
      height: 100%;
      object-fit: cover;
    }
    .product-thumbs {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
      gap: 0.75rem;
      margin-top: 1rem;
    }
    .product-thumb {
      border-radius: var(--radius);
      overflow: hidden;
      aspect-ratio: 1;
      cursor: pointer;
      border: 2px solid transparent;
      transition: var(--transition);
      background: var(--white);
    }
    .product-thumb:hover,
    .product-thumb.active {
      border-color: var(--gold);
      box-shadow: 0 4px 12px rgba(201,146,42,0.25);
    }
    .product-thumb img {
      width: 100%;
      height: 100%;
      object-fit: cover;
    }
    .product-info {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0;
    }
    .product-badge {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.5rem;
      background: rgba(201,146,42,0.14);
      border: 1px solid rgba(201,146,42,0.35);
      color: var(--gold-dark);
